<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="Y" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Yard" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Yard,</orth> 1) a measure of three feet: <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 109</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.273" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 273</bibl> <cit><quote>(tailor's y.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 2, 40</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.208" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 89</bibl> <cit><quote>(a clothier's y.). two --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 44</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 44</bibl> <cit><quote>eight --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 26</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 50</bibl>. <cit><quote>four y.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 66</bibl></cit> (Fluellen's speech). <cit><quote>loves her by the foot. He may not by the y.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.676" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 676</bibl></cit> (with an indecent quibble).<lb />2) a piece of timber by which a sail is extended: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.200" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 200</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>